EUNICE
Where's the key?
MARIA JOSÉ
Does it even have one?
She yanks at the gate, but it won't budge. Maria José puts
down the hose and tries to help.
EUNICE
Let me do it.
Maria José steps back, surprised at her reaction. Eunice puts
Pimpão down and heaves the gate shut. Both women go in. The
water from the hose keeps on trickling down the sidewalk.
INT. PAIVA FAMILY HOME / LAUNDRY ROOM - DAY
Maria José is ironing clothes next to the radio playing a
