In the bathroom, Eunice scrubs her hands under hot water.
INT. PAIVA FAMILY HOME / STUDY - LATE NIGHT
Rain. Eunice rereads the writ of habeas corpus. There are
notes in the margins, and she's jotting down observations. As
she lights a cigarette, there's a noise at the door.
Startled, she slowly straightens up in the chair.
INT. PAIVA FAMILY HOME / LIVING ROOM - LATE NIGHT
Headlights rake across the dark room. Through the wet window,
Eunice spots a car idling outside.
A FIGURE comes out of the car and up to the house. Eunice
quietly makes sure the front door is locked. An envelope is
slipped under the door, addressed simply to EUNICE.
She opens the door, and her eyes meet Martha's through the
car window before the vehicle vanishes down the dark, empty
street.
67.
68.
INT. PAIVA FAMILY HOME / STUDY - LATE NIGHT
The torn envelope lies on top of the scale model of the
